    <title>Tech CEOs want to replicate Tim Cook’s Donald Trump playbook</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="US President Donald Trump (r) and Apple CEO Tim Cook speak to the press during a tour of the Flextronics computer manufacturing facility where Apple’s Mac Pros are assembled in Austin, Texas, on November 20, 2019." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Wx-FvwRlXrkjsrIHeZfBGtlXTgg=/0x0:5568x3712/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73744918/1183652392.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tim Cook and then-President Donald Trump, speaking to the Press in Austin, Texas in 2019.&lt;/em&gt; | Photo: Mandel Ngan / AFP via Getty Images&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="JMUdGG"&gt;Apple CEO Tim Cook managed to forge a personal relationship with Donald Trump during his first Presidential term that other tech firms struggled to replicate. Now, others are trying to follow his template, says a &lt;a href="https://www.wsj.com/politics/elections/tim-cook-ceo-trump-relationship-ad106f36"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wall Street Journal &lt;/em&gt;report&lt;/a&gt; today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="VIHzJP"&gt;Cook used direct appeals to influence Trump’s 2017 tax policy and to get him to dial back his 2019 tariffs in &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/20/20973991/trump-tim-cook-apple-friendship-tax-cuts-china-tariffs-manufacturing-jobs"&gt;ways that benefitted Apple&lt;/a&gt;. In exchange, Trump got to look good; as the &lt;em&gt;Journal&lt;/em&gt; points out, Cook didn’t correct Trump when claimed responsibility for Apple opening an Austin manufacturing plant that had already been around for years and &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2019/11/20/20974999/trump-is-lying-about-the-new-apple-factory"&gt;wasn’t even owned by Apple&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="0TxK7v"&gt;Part of Cook’s strategy was keeping things simple, according to the &lt;em&gt;Journal&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p id="XtP9oK"&gt;Instead of sending government relations...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
